386→                        <div id="content">Let $A(x)$ count the number of $n\leq x$ which are the sum of two squarefull numbers (a number $m$ is squarefull if $p\mid m$ implies $p^2\mid m$). Is it true that\[A(x) \sim c \frac{x}{\sqrt{\log x}}\]for some $c&#62;0$?</div>
