406→                           Odoni <a href="#cite-Od81-1081" onclick="event.preventDefault();addNewBox('Od81','1081'); return false;">[Od81]</a> proved this is false, and that\[A(x) \gg \exp\left(c\frac{\log\log\log x}{\log\log x}\right)\frac{x}{\sqrt{\log x}}\]for some constant $c&gt;0$. Estimates for $A(x)$ have been improved by Baker and Brudern <a href="#cite-BaBr94-1081" onclick="event.preventDefault();addNewBox('BaBr94','1081'); return false;">[BaBr94]</a>, Blomer <a href="#cite-Bl04-1081" onclick="event.preventDefault();addNewBox('Bl04','1081'); return false;">[Bl04]</a>, and most recently by Blomer and Granville <a href="#cite-BlGr06-1081" onclick="event.preventDefault();addNewBox('BlGr06','1081'); return false;">[BlGr06]</a>, who proved\[A(x)= (\log\log x)^{O(1)}\frac{x}{(\log x)^{\alpha}}\]where $\alpha=1-2^{-1/3}\approx 0.206299$.<br><br>See also <a href="/940" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer ugc" target="_blank">[940]</a>.
